'''埃莫斯·塔克工商管理学院'''（{{lang-en|Amos Tuck School of Business Administration}}，常簡稱為'''塔克商学院'''）是[[美国|美国]][[达特茅斯学院|达特茅斯学院]]的一所商科[[研究生|研究生]]院，坐落在[[新罕布什尔州|新罕布什尔州]]汉诺威市。该院创建于1900年，是世界最早的商学研究生院，也是第一所颁发工商管理[[硕士研究生|硕士研究生]]学位的学院<ref>{{cite web |url=http://alumni.yale.edu/clubs/fapn/2001_04_09_WSJ.html |title=And the Winner Is... Dartmouth's Tuck School |first=Ron |last=Alsop |date=2001-04-09 |publisher=CareerJournal.com: The Wall Street Journal Executive Career Site |accessdate=2007-11-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120707190438/http://alumni.yale.edu/clubs/fapn/2001_04_09_WSJ.html |archivedate=2012-07-07 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.stanfordalumni.org/news/magazine/2001/janfeb/departments/upfront/lettoed.html | title = Make That Third | first = Frederick | last = Webster, Jr. | work = Stanford Alumni Magazine | date = January/February 2001 | accessdate = 2007-11-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080123203503/http://www.stanfordalumni.org/news/magazine/2001/janfeb/departments/upfront/lettoed.html | archive-date = 2008-01-23 | dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.dartmo.com/archives/303 | title = Business Education History | first = Scott | last = Meacham | work = Dartmo.com: The Buildings of Dartmouth College | accessdate = 2007-11-09 | archive-date = 2019-12-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191228024055/http://www.dartmo.com/archives/303 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://business.collegesurfing.com/content/cat/183 |title=Business Schools |publisher=CollegeSurfing.com |accessdate=2007-11-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080704191108/http://business.collegesurfing.com/content/cat/183 |archivedate=2008-07-04 }}</ref>。达特茅斯学院是美国六所[[常春藤联盟商学院|常春藤院校联盟]]成员之一。在众多商科院校工商管理硕士教育排名中，该院位居前五，是世界一流商学院之一。<ref name="rankings">{{cite web | url = http://www.tuck.dartmouth.edu/news/rankings.html | title = MBA Program Rankings | publisher = Tuck School of Business | accessdate = 2007-11-06 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071028085541/http://www.tuck.dartmouth.edu/news/rankings.html | archivedate = 2007-10-28 }}</ref>

塔克商学院本身只授予学生[[工商管理硕士|工商管理硕士]]（[[MBA|MBA]]）一种学位，但它同时与其它教育机构合作办学，为学生提供双学位机会，也为职员和刚毕业的大学生提供短期培训。该院极为注重自己紧密专注与[[寄宿|寄宿]]制的办学特色，设有46个全日制科系，学生总数稳定在500人左右。<ref name="about tuck">{{cite web | url = http://www.tuck.edu/about/index.html | title = About Tuck | publisher = Tuck School of Business | accessdate = 2007-11-09 | archive-date = 2010-08-30 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100830214256/http://www.tuck.edu/about/index.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>院方宣称超过8400名塔克毕业生活跃在各行各业，校友为学校提供的捐赠居所有商学院之首。

== 历史 ==
[[File:Edward_Tuck.jpg|thumb]]
19世纪末，美国的工业和经济发展迅速，越来越多的大学毕业生选择进入商界。达特茅斯大学校长威廉·杰威特·塔克尔（{{lang|en|William Jewett Tucker}}）为顺应这一需求，决定在校内兴建一所商学院。<ref name="jstor">{{cite web | url = http://www.jstor.org/view/00221546/di962315/96p0045s/0 | title = The Amos Tuck School of Business Administration: Its Origin and Present Program | first = Karl A. | last = Hill | work = Journal of Higher Education | volume = XXXII | accessdate = 2007-11-08 |date=December 1961}}</ref>为实现这一计划，塔克尔开始寻求大学室友爱德华·塔克（{{lang|en|Edward Tuck}}）的支持。塔克是一位富有的银行家和慈善家，<ref name="our history">{{cite web|url=http://www.tuck.edu/about/history/index.html |title=About Tuck: Our History |publisher=Tuck School of Business |accessdate=2007-11-08 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070524141711/http://www.tuck.edu/about/history/index.html |archivedate=2007-05-24 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>他将价值30万美元的[[明尼苏达|明尼苏达]]铁路公司优先股捐给达特茅斯大学，作为商学院的建设资金。学院名称以塔克的父亲、达特茅斯大学校友埃莫斯·塔克的名字命名为“埃莫斯·塔克工商管理与金融学院”。<ref name="our history"/>

[[File:Amos_tuck.jpg|thumb]]
新成立的塔克商学院每学年学费为100美元，开办第一年入学的学生不多，他们在两年课程结束后获发商科[[硕士学位|硕士学位]]文凭<ref name="tuck history timeline"/><ref name="our history"/>。学院课程涵盖传统的[[博雅教育|博雅教育]]、经济学和[[金融|金融]]学<ref name="jstor"/>。学生在第一学年的大部分课程由本院教授讲授，第二学年则由外聘导师和商界人士讲授。作为美国第一所商科研究生院，塔克强调全面化的教学模式，这种模式为许多新兴的其他商科院校所采纳，被称为“塔克模式”。<ref name="jstor"/><ref name="our history"/>

1920年代晚期，达特茅斯大学校长恩纳斯特·马丁·霍普金斯（{{lang|en|Ernest Martin Hopkins}}）为突出商学院的整体性，拟修建中心校园，将教学和住宿设施集中。当时居于法国、年事已高的爱德华·塔克再次为学院建设捐出了57万美元<ref name="our history"/>。1929年，塔克就是受益于这笔捐款，在达特茅斯大学校园西侧建起了4幢崭新的大楼。<ref name="our history"/><ref name="our history"/><ref name="dartmo-tuck">{{cite web |url=http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/tuvwxyzbldg.html#tuckhall2 |title=Tuck Hall (II) |work=Dartmo.: The Buildings of Dartmouth College |accessdate=2007-10-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120907222737/http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/tuvwxyzbldg.html#tuckhall2 |archivedate=2012-09-07 }}</ref>

1942年，学院名称变更为埃莫斯塔克工商管理学院；1953年，毕业生的学位名称也转变为[[现代|现代]]意义的[[工商管理硕士|工商管理硕士]]（[[MBA|MBA]]）。直至20世纪50年代末和60年代初，塔克主要还是面向达特茅斯大学校内招生，接受本科三年级的学生入读MBA课程；之后，在卡尔·希尔院长（1957年-1960年在任）的倡导下，商学院将招生范围扩大到全国。约翰·亨尼斯（{{lang|en|John Hennessey}}，1968年-1976年在任）继任院长后，学院的扩建进一步持续。1960年代晚期，校园建设呈现突飞猛进的势头，新宿舍（1969年）和默多中心（1973年，含费德堡商务和工程图书馆）相继落成。后来的院长理查德·威斯特（{{lang|en|Richard West}}，1976年–1983年在任）和科林·布莱登（{{lang|en|Colin Blaydon}}，1983年–1990年在任）对学院的课程设置和科、系建设进行了暴发性扩张，申请入院的学生增长了三分之一<ref name="our history"/>。1980年代以来，学院在学生数量和硬件设施方面持续扩张，除两幢新校舍外，若干个科研中心也建成使用；学院还在校内实施非学历性商科教育计划。<ref name="tuck history timeline"/>

== 校园及其建筑 ==
塔克商学院坐落在[[达特茅斯大学|达特茅斯大学]]西面，毗邻[[康乃狄克河|康乃狄克河]]，地处[[新罕布什尔州|新罕布什尔州]]汉诺威市新英格兰镇的乡村地带，北面是康乃狄克河河谷<ref name="our_campus">{{cite web|url=http://www.tuck.dartmouth.edu/about/campus/index.html |title=Our Campus |publisher=Tuck School of Business |accessdate=2007-11-06 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071101051834/http://www.tuck.dartmouth.edu/about/campus/index.html |archivedate=2007-11-01 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。1900年，新成立的商学院设立于面对达特茅斯大学中央草坪的一座单一大楼内<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/lmnopbldg.html#mcnutthall | title = McNutt Hall | work = Dartmo.: The Buildings of Dartmouth College | accessdate = 2007-11-06 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20040904083031/http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/lmnopbldg.html#mcnutthall | archivedate = 2004-09-04 }}</ref>。1930年，学院的教学机构、办公设施迁进了斯特尔（Stell）、切斯（Chase）、塔克（Tuck）和武德伯里（Woodbury）大楼内，这些大楼均分布在今日的塔克行政大楼周围<ref name="dartmo-tuck"/><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/cdbldg.html#chasehouse | title = Chase House | work = Dartmo.: The Buildings of Dartmouth College | accessdate = 2007-10-02 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20040622180337/http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/cdbldg.html#chasehouse | archivedate = 2004-06-22 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/qrsbldg.html#stellhall |title=Stell Hall |work=Dartmo.: The Buildings of Dartmouth College |accessdate=2007-10-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120723142429/http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/qrsbldg.html#stellhall |archivedate=2012-07-23 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/tuvwxyzbldg.html#woodburyhouse |title=Woodbury House |work=Dartmo.: The Buildings of Dartmouth College |accessdate=2007-10-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120907222737/http://www.dartmo.com/buildings/tuvwxyzbldg.html#woodburyhouse |archivedate=2012-09-07 }}</ref>。直至今日，学院八个科系中的四个，仍在原先的这些建筑物内教学和办公。<ref name="our_campus"/>

学院注重自己的寄宿制办学特色，并将这一特色阐述为“塔克文化”的基石，指出“塔克毕业生能在世界所有商学院中表现出最高的忠诚度的原因”（援引）也归功于此<ref name="our_campus"/><ref name="strategy">{{cite web|url=http://www.tuck.edu/about/strategy.html |title=About Tuck: Our Strategy |publisher=Tuck School of Business |accessdate=2007-11-08 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070524141916/http://www.tuck.edu/about/strategy.html |archivedate=2007-05-24 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。学院以其相对封闭、独立的乡村校园环境来吸引优秀学生和教师，虽然有些学生认为这种环境可以增进学生的亲密感和友谊，但被外界描述为“形象问题”<ref name="tuckies">{{cite news | url = http://www.careerjournal.com/specialreports/bschool03/articles/20020909-alsop-mbtuck.html | title = Dartmouth's Tuck School Keeps Challengers at Bay | first = Ronald | last = Alsop | publisher = CareerJournal.com: The Wall Street Journal Executive Career Site | year = 2003 | accessdate = 2007-11-08 | archive-date = 2008-01-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080123081408/http://www.careerjournal.com/specialreports/bschool03/articles/20020909-alsop-mbtuck.html | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="pr-sl&e">{{cite web|url=http://www.princetonreview.com/mba/research/profiles/studentsSay.asp?listing=1010998&category=6&LTID=2 |title=What Tuck Students Say About... Student Life and Environment |publisher=The Princeton Review |accessdate=2007-11-10 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080123062811/http://www.princetonreview.com/mba/research/profiles/studentsSay.asp?listing=1010998&category=6&LTID=2 |archivedate=2008-01-23|deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

塔克商学院有三处寄宿楼：惠特莫尔大楼（Whittemore Hall，2000年建成）、埃科特米尔大楼（Achtmeyer Hall，2008年建成）和皮罗-瓦朗谢纳大楼（Pineau-Valencienne Hall，2008年建成）。这些新近落成的寄宿大楼和雷泽尔大楼（Raether Hall）是塔克综合楼的组成部分，有85名计划外学生在此学习、居住。塔克综合楼建造费用2720万美元，2008年12月落成。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.dartmouth.edu/~opdc/projects/llc/index.html | title = Tuck School Living and Learning Complex | publisher = Office of Planning, Design and Construction | accessdate = 2007-10-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071219013600/http://www.dartmouth.edu/~opdc/projects/llc/index.html | archive-date = 2007-12-19 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>塔克商学院与邻近的塞耶工程学院共同使用默多中心（Murdough Center）（包括费德堡商务与工程图书馆）<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuck.dartmouth.edu/about/campus/murdough.html |title=About Tuck - Murdough Center |publisher=Tuck School of Business |accessdate=2007-11-06 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071105111142/http://www.tuck.dartmouth.edu/about/campus/murdough.html |archivedate=2007-11-05|deadurl=yes }}</ref>。伯恩大楼管理处负责塔克校园的管理与服务，学院食堂则由达特茅斯饮食服务中心运营。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dartmouth.edu/~dds/text/byrnehall.shtml |title=Dining Locations - Byrne Hall |publisher=Dartmouth Dining Services |accessdate=2007-11-06 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071101045554/http://www.dartmouth.edu/~dds/text/byrnehall.shtml |archivedate=2007-11-01|deadurl=yes }}</ref>

2009年，布肯南大楼（Buchanan Hall，1968年建成）被整修一新，其功能由原来的学生宿舍转变为学术研讨机构和职员公寓综合楼。学院计划在接下来的5年内，增加10名全职教工，这些新增加的教工将入住布肯南大楼。<ref>[http://www.dartmouth.edu/~opdc/projects/buchanan/index.html "Buchanan Hall Renovation"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dartmouth.edu/~opdc/projects/buchanan/index.html |date=20100824034832 }}, Office of Planning, Design and Construction, April 4, 2009, accessed January 17, 2011.</ref>
